author: @bbang_dduck1
text:
언젠가 이 영상이 많은 뮤지션과 프로듀서, 그리고 또 연습생, 현 아이돌들에게 중요한 자료화면으로 쓰일날이 온다고 본다.

현존 남돌 중 감히 투탑이라해도 과언이 아닌 팀의 천재 프로듀서의 만남.

그리고 정말 앞으로가 더 기대되고 기다려지는 뮤지션들이라 방탄과 세븐틴이 지금도 물론 넘치게 멋지지만 지금보다도 더 kpop을 알리고 최정상에 서는 그 때. 
이 영상을 다시 보고싶을것 같다.

본인들의 신념과 팀에 대한 마음, 음악에 대한 관념 그리고 무한히 감사해하며 신뢰를 지키려는 팬덤에대한 마음까지... 그냥 뭐랄까 내가 이 두 팀이 존재하는 나라에 살고 있다는게 무한히 감사하다.

author: @emeraldg.391
text:
I've been rewatching Suchwita episodes lately, because I miss Yoongi, and this particular episode, because today is​ Jihoon's birthday, and I must​ ​say it's so healing to do so!💗 I'm so grateful we have this show and new episodes to enjoy!💗
I have such deep admiration and respect for both Yoongi and Jihoon not just for being incredibly talented artists, but for their genuine and honest, passionate and considerate, dedicated, humble and inspiring personalities, their viewpoints and attitude towards different things and situations in life.
This is so amazing seeing them interact with each other like this! Truly they are like brothers, and their thoughts are so​ aligned that it even made Jihoon feel astonished, they have so much in common! Actually, seeing Yoongi praising Jihoon and showing his respect towards him and them developing such a special bond is so heart-warming, it's just like you've witnessed the 8th wonder of the world!💗 Yoongi is always such a kind and considerate host!💗 And, of course, it would be just beyond epic if their collaboration as 'Brothers' would​ become a reality! We would absolutely love it!☺❤️‍🔥
Infinite love ❤

author: @izanami16
text:
А ничего, что я не пью алкоголь? :) 🙈 Поэтому я буду пить сыворотку с вами🥛
Настало время моего счастья - поучиться уму-разуму у Сюги❤ моя отдушина😊
Спасибо, что знакомите нас с новыми людьми и радуете нас общением, дарите нам свет☀
...вот так совпадение - несколько выпусков молчала, что не пью и только решила написать, как гость тоже не пьёт😀
Так как я присоединилась недавно, мои просмотры и комменты будут в обратном порядке в видео бантан:)
Уджи и Сюга - да, ещё пока не сказали, я заметила, есть некоторые похожие черты.
Еда🤩
Мин-страдамус😃🥰 ну хоть не я одна этим занимаюсь😅
Наделала себе скринов кофточки Сюги - глаз радует😍 Она выглядит, как хэнд-мэйд, словно вышивка - ручная работа. Вроде и ярко, и мои любимые золотые нитки, но глаз успокаивает.
Какое-то время сидела на компьютерных играх, потом перестала. Я понимаю их - зачем развлечения, если есть любимое дело, которое и есть хобби. Тоже вроде и занимаюсь тем, что другие сочтут скучным, но мне нравится заниматься своей профессией с упоением - фильмы и игры не дотягивают до изучения моих любимых, для всех - нудных, научных книжек😁 Сейчас вдохновляете меня осваивать профессию - вы❤
Спасибо вашему приятному и милому гостю за эти посиделки🌼
Я уж промолчу, как хочу, чтобы БТС были вместе всю жизнь (мою), итак по этому поводу ныла в разных видео😃
В конце Сюга сматерился😆😅 БТС наверное, единственные, от кого мне это мило и весело😆

author: @ayu_gyu
text:
"The world looks so beautiful from the outside & it seems to run well but if you look inside, everyone's trying so hard to get through it (Fvck but fight for my life)" - Woozi 2023

After recent events when we lost someone precious to us, we can see the dark side of K-Pop, everything looks bright & happy from the outside but from the inside there's so much struggle from constant practice, extreme diet, no dating, maintaining a perfect image & face, being hated by antis, treated unfairly, so many restrictions that one can lose sight of what they had wanted before & questioning whether it was worth it, the things they love the most is now a job. This is not just applicable to them but to every one of us. I hope this message in the song reaches a lot of people & they can think positively.

author: @dianamontoya4413
text:
Watching this interview was very interesting. Apparently both boys already knew each other quite well, but for reasons of their respective agencies, they had not been able to meet in public. Finally, agency stuff. On the other hand, and being honest, we needed to talk more about Woozi and less about Suga. I think if a person hosts a talk show, they should listen to the person they are hosting and talk less about themselves. I guess that's the writer's fault more than Suga's, but if it seemed to me then, they should have made a second part.
There were too many things to mention, things that would explain the reason for several decisions by Woozi and Pledis. Among them is the fact that this boy is fluent in several instruments, sang in a choir as a child, and can also read music. And that's just a bit of what he failed to mention, mostly because there wasn't an opportunity to do so, and also, Woozi is a very modest man.
I hope they do a second part, because it's really worth getting to know Woozi more deeply, and if Suga does the interview, I guess it will give us the pleasure of seeing them together again.

author: @chus8634
text: 나한텐 이 컨텐츠가 개인적으로는 거의 역사적이라고 평가할 수 있을 컨텐츠다. 나는 14년도부터 아티스트 민윤기와 방탄을 응원했고, 윤기 덕분에 우연히 15년도의 아직은 조금 어렸던 우지를 알게 되었다. 아주 가볍게 응원할 수 있을 마음일 줄 알고 세븐틴을 응원하기 시작했는데 내 선견지명이 반만 있었던 거지. 지금 내게 가장 좋아하는, 존경하는 아티스트이자 인간이 누구냐 물어보면 나는 주저하지 않고 우지라고 말한다. 누군가를 통해서 좋아하게 된 마음이 이제는 내가 가진 여러 감정들 중 어디에 빗댈 수도 없이 크고 단단해져 버려 결국 나라는 사람을 이루는 아주 중요한 요소가 되었다. 내게 청소년기를 말하라면 방탄과 민윤기를 빼놓을 수 없고, 내게 청년기와 남은 인생을 말하라면 우지와 세븐틴을 빼놓을 수 없다. 나의 인생에 가장 까다로운 변곡점을 함께 걸어주고, 가장 다채로운 색을 주고, 가장 극단적인 순간들에 나를 현실로 이끌어 준 이 두 사람에게 나는 더없이 감사함을 표하고 싶다. 그러기 위해 내가 할 수 있는 일은 지금까지 그랬듯 변함없는 믿음으로 기다리고 응원하며 미래를 또한 함께 기다리는 것이리라. 이 컨텐츠는 그것을 위한 아주 작은 동기부여의 조각이 될 것이다. 누군가에겐 여한이 없을 정도로 소중한 컨텐츠를 만들어준 제작진과 두 출연자 민윤기, 이지훈에게 다시 한번 감사와 깊은 애정을 보낸다.

author: @madamec1990
text:
Dear Woozi.

Aku sudah mengikuti Seventeen sejak era 'Mansae'. Alasan aku jadi "Carat" karena aku merasa semua lagu yang dirilis Seventeen itu seolah-olah diciptakan khusus untukku, dan aku juga sangat suka tarian dan penampilan Seventeen saat di atas panggung. Aku bukan penggemar awalnya, tapi aku suka semua lagu yang dirilis oleh Seventeen. Aku menunggu kalian 'comeback" dengan sangat excited, perasaan itu masih aku rasakan sampai sekarang. Perasaan bersemangat dan penuh harapan setiap kali kalian 'Comeback" tidak pernah berubah sejak tahun 2016. Aku pernah khawatir 'apakah aku akan tetap menyukai lagu-lagu seventeen jika Seventeen berganti genre/tema?' tapi anehnya, jenis lagu apapun yang kalian rilis .. aku masih merasa lagu itu diciptakan khusus untukku. Semua lagu itu seakan-akan diletakan di dalam kotak kado, dan ketika aku membukanya ... tadaa! itu adalah hadiah yang sangat aku sukai, seakan-akan sang pengirim tahu bahwa hadiah ini adalah hadiah yang telah lama aku nantikan.

 
Teruntuk Woozi dan semua member Seventeen yang sudah bekerja keras selama ini, terima kasih banyak untuk semua karya yang telah kalian berikan. Kami (Carat) selalu menjadi orang-orang yang mendukung kalian, jadi kalian tidak perlu khawatir dan hanya perlu menikmati pekerjaan kalian.

Seperti bagian perasaan bahagia yang diberikan Seventeen untukku yang tidak pernah berubah sejak awal, aku harap Seventeen juga tidak kehilangan perasaan senang, antusias, dan berdebar penuh antisipasi saat tampil di atas panggung. Aku harap kalian bisa selalu menikmati pekerjaan kalian sebagaimana aku menikmati hasil karya yang telah kalian berikan.

Seventeen, fighting!

author: @say_the_name_17_
text:
얼마나 기다린거야 이 조합... 너무 완전 작은 슈가(우지)랑 큰 우지(슈가)잖어... 슈가님도 방탄 멤버들이랑 있을땐 작아보이셨는데 우지랑 있으니까 생각보다 크시네요ㅋㅋㅋ

진짜 이 영상 보고 하고싶은 말이 너무너무 많지만... 조금 줄여서 말해보자면! 난 우리 우지가 너무 자랑스러워요. 겨우 중학생 때 부산에서 서울까지 올라와 성공해야한다는 목표 하나만을 가지고 힘든 연습생 생활을 견뎌낸것도, 고작 노트북 하나와 작곡 앱 하나로 작곡을 시작해 지금의 프로듀서 우지가 된 것도, 우리 세븐틴에게 '자체 제작돌'이라는 멋진 별명이 붙게 된것도 전부 다 너무 많이 자랑스러워요.  그리고 또.. 이런거 정말 싫지만 이제 슬슬 짧은 작별을 고해야 할 시기가 다가오고 있잖아요? 정말 확실하게 말하는데, 우리 캐럿들 절대로 어디 안가요. 어딜 가긴 무슨 여기 꼭 붙어서 기다릴거에요. 그리고 돌아와주면 언제나처럼 반겨줄게요. 그니까 돌아만 와요. 우린 항상 여기 있다는거 꼭 기억하고. 이제 세븐틴은 내 삶에서 절대로 뗴어낼 수 없는 소중한 일부에요. 내 일부가 되어줘서 정말 고마워요. 영원히 사랑해요 진심으로ㅎㅎ 세븐틴은 행복만 했으면 좋겠다 정말로.

author: @cristhalcuayita3619
text: Aquí algo que a nadie le interesa: Recuerdo que cuando recién entraba al mundo kpop (yo buscaba así: 'música de Japón; música de corea..." por un proyecto de mi escuela, no es broma) primero fuí a Youtube, y en primera plana apareció BTS, pero como los cantantes masculinos de por acá en Latinoamérica no me gustan mucho (más que los que cantan baladas) pues como que me dió miedito entrar a ver, entonces la siguiente opción era bp, y así es como mi primer acercamiento fué bmbyah (sé que a Army no le interesa esto, pero aquí viene lo q si importa 😂:) Fuí a Google a buscar de kpop porque realmente si me enganché con la canción aquella, ahí ví que el grupo más famoso en Billboard era BTS, y ahí voy a buscar en Wikipedia información sobre esa boy band, y me enteré que tiene canciones que no son del típico tema amoroso, sino de temas sociales y de autoestima. Ahí dije esto si me interesa, y busqué la letra traducida de unas canciones de Bangtan que alguna página recomendaba, y ví la letra en cierta página que no usan precisamente para escribir letras, sino no velas. Entre títulos parecidos me perdí. No entendí nada porque antes de BTS yo no hacía streaming de nada, ni me interesaba los proyectos alternos que un cantante podría tener, pero sí me llamó la atención una publicación con imágenes que decía "Woozi - hermano menor de Suga" y todos estaban riendo porque efectivamente se parecen, y algunos despistados cómo yo creían que si lo eran, hasta que leían sobre el deseo de los fans de ver interacción entre ambos en la realidad y entendí q ellos nada q ver. Ahora que recuerdo eso, me da risa porque digo "Sí manifestaron" :D y saber las cosas que tienen en común como que ambos son productores... Men, sólo la sangre y sus grupos los separan

Para mi este ha sido uno de los episodios que no quería que terminara.
La conversación entre ambos fluyó de una manera tan natural que te hacía conectar con sus pensamientos, y es que no es para menos, porque ambos tienen en común el ser increíbles artistas (en todo el sentido de la palabra), escriben, producen, cantan, bailan y sobre todo siempre tienen presente a sus grupos y a sus fans.
Nunca me arrepentiré de ser CARAT y ARMY, porque sin duda alguna, admiro todo el talento que tienen, y el trabajo y la dedicación que le ponen a todo lo que hacen.
Son los mejores de la industria y merecen mucho éxito. 🥹💜🤝🏻🩷🩵
BTS, SEVENTEEN FIGHTING! ✨️

author: @Sebisajiminstan
text:
I absolutely love how much Seventeen just. Love each other? You can clearly tell both SVT and BTS have this in common— the group is always the number one priority. Period. And it’s been obvious for years now, how not one member out of the 7, nor the 13, has ever tried standing out in a group promotion. Which makes them more coherent, which makes the group itself stand out. I think there are multiple factors to their succes, of course, but i feel like this is an important part of it. Fans will feel that energy and respond to it. 
We’re seeing now how BTS deals with their separation, and i hope they can lend some advice to SVT for when the time comes. 
Also, can’t tell you how glad i am this show finally brought these two groups in contact, even if it’s just Hoshi, Woozi and Yoongi as of now. While I can’t call myself a carat, i have been a fan of Seventeen since 2015, and they are the only other group aside from BTS I actively listen to constantly, so this long awaited crossover makes me so incredibly happy. Like, you can tell Yoongi is so taken with both Hoshi and Woozi, now. He mentioned Hoshi 4? 5? times lool.

author: @wheeloffortune2908
text: This is such interesting episode for me as a carat. Woozi is my bias. Woozi doesn't often appear in variety or talk shows (I believe that''s partly because of himself chose not) so to have him wants to come to Suchwita is a treat for me. And he also doesn't drink, so when I saw he'll be in Suchwita I thought "Ah, will it be okay...?" I'm glad my worry is unnecessary. I'm very impressed how Suga as the host is attentive, asking about the guests and encourage them to talk about themselves, really kind and welcoming. Which makes me really glad because other than his personal lives in vlives/weverse playing guides of SVT songs, talking about tidbits of music making, Woozi indeed very rarely talk about it. I'm grateful he appears in Suchwita and be able to talk and share thoughts about music with Suga, a respected senior and producer in industry, who understands struggles and other things as idol and producer, we as a fan don't understand. SVT holds BTS in high regards, as Hoshi said BTS changed the game and playing field in Kpop and for many. So this tiny exchanges we can see here means the world. Thank you Suga and Suchwita (and ARMY) for having Woozi here. 🩷🩵🩷🩵🩷🩵ς(>‿<.)

author: @princess2124
text: Seventeen was supposed to debut with 17 members but the line up never happened. So instead seventeen stands for 13 members+ 3 units(vocal, hiphop & performance)+ 1 team.

author: @hikariai917
text:
Pledis intended to go with 17members,however as time passed, 13 members were ready to debut. Thus, these 13 members came out with the definition of a 3-team unit that is Hiphop unit,Performance unit, and Vocal unit. Still, they are 1 team all together. 

17 also signify their journey from trainee, their youth. That is how Seventeen (17) is a group with thirteen members

author: @tempest0.0.0
text:
Also alternately, the last 1 also symbolizes 1 as a team in 18= 13+ 3+1
I explained it as carat but it is in both senses.

author: @aridolores
text:
What I like about this is when Woozi said that he makes music that the members like, and in turn it is music that CARATS like.

It aligns with my principle that you make music for yourself, and that sincerity and genuineness will reflect with the listeners and fans you gain.

I think that's one of the perks of being an idol producer, having some control on the color of the music you bring into the group.

author: @tempest0.0.0
text: It also reflects how the fans like their idols for a reason. How not only the song turns out great but it also just matches the fans' taste. It kinda (in a sense) portrays the similarities b/w the members' and their fans' choice of music. That the fans don't just like whatever is presented in front of them just because their faves are presenting it. It's regarding the effort that the musicians put in at their level best to present something, which is why they are liked.

author: @yunabom5625
text:
지훈아, 너가 이 댓글을 봐줄 지 모르겠지만 말야😊
오늘 세븐틴 축복이 내려앉은 영상에서 드물게 눈물이 나오더라.
데뷔 때부터 슈가 님과 닮았다며 여러번 화제됐었고, 나도 이 만남을 너무 고대해왔던 터라 너무 기대됐어. 그냥 즐겁게 보고싶었는데 이지훈이 기어코 날 울려버렸네😂
뭐랄까, 하고싶은 말이 너무 많은데, 음..
자랑스러운 우리 보보, 우리 지훈아!
20살에 데뷔했는데 우리 지후니 벌써 28살이야
연차가 들어갈수록 아기 때 얼굴이 남아있으면서도 점점 슈가 님과 분위기가 비슷해져가는 게 보이고😊
아무튼, 내가 데뷔팬은 아니지만 말야.. 사실 데뷔팬이면 더 좋을 것 같은데 미안해.. 그땐 아이돌에 큰 관심을 보이지 않았었거든.
내가 그리 긴 삶을 살아온 건 아니지만, 살면서 처음으로 열렬히 좋아했던 아이돌이 세븐틴이고, 지금까지도 이렇게 꾸준히 사랑하고 있는 아이돌도 세븐틴이 거의 유일한 것 같아. 
고맙다 컴백했던 날이 2018년 2월 5일이었지, 나 그날 캐럿이 돼버렸단 걸 인정했다?
사실 인정하고보니까 그날이 컴백날이었더라고 ㅋㅋㅋ
어쨌든, 내 노래 취향이 어떻게 되냐고 누가 물어보면 난 세븐틴 노래라고 답해. 진짜로 모든 노래가 다 너무 내 취향이라서.
이게 다 우리 천재 작곡가 우지 덕분 아니겠어?❤
아무튼, 난 데뷔팬도, 8년차 캐럿도 아니지만, 올해 6년차 캐럿으로서, 진짜 진심으로 평생 캐럿으로 살고싶어. 물론 그렇게 살거고!
그러니까 지훈아, 너무 무리하지말고. 캐럿들은 언제나 환영하고 맞아줄 준비 다 되어있으니까.
사실 언젠가부터 활동기간이 많이 짧아진 것에 대해서 너무 아쉽다고 느꼈었는데, 그럼에도 불구하고 아직까지도 1년에 2번씩 꼬박꼬박 컴백해주고 있어서 너무 고마워.
아 진짜 이지훈 날 제대로 울려버렸어😂
너무 길어진 것 같다.. 하고싶은 말은 끝도 없는데..
핵심은 그거야. 캐럿들은 언제나 세븐틴이라는 다이아몬드를 빛내주기 위해 늘 곁에서 기다리고 있으니까!!
너무 걱정하지 말고, 부담갖지도 말고.
나 올해 들어서 고3이라고 여기저기 광고하고 다녀서 우지도 한번쯤 보지 않았을까..? 세븐틴 영상에서도 자주 했는데😆
아직 한번도 세븐틴 공식 오프 행사에 가본 적이 없는데.. 나 진짜 수능 끝나면 바로 티켓팅해서 실물 보러 갈거니까..!!
나 가서도 이런 내용 담은 편지도 전해주고 우지 예쁘다 귀엽다 멋있다 해버릴거야!! 알겠지? 그러니까 기다려줘😊
사랑하고 지훈아, 그냥.. 모르겠다, 우아해❤

And when I thought I can’t admire WOOZI even more, this ep just proves me wrong ALL OVER again. WOOZI’s dedication and passion for music and seventeen is crazy. Like he even thought of the title ‘producer’ as too heavy of a word for him but the truth is he is fully AND WELL DESERVING of this title. And his reason to accept it was that since CARATS are really proud of this he should be proud and acknowledge it😭😭 but still being the humblest man, I’ve never seen him boast or talk about this status anywhere, it’s always the members who bring it up and praise him about it (seventeen friendship goals 😭😭) and the members all putting SEVENTEEN as the utmost priority ALL THE TIME when they are already 9 years down the road is just sosososo heartwarming to me 🥺🥺 I’m so grateful that I am a fan of this wonderful group and will continue to support them on this flower path for as long as it can be <3 im sure all CARATS feel the same way too :D

text: @SimplySimran Dude, I know all the compositing programs! Do you even realize what a "Garage Band" is?! It's so unprofessional and it's for kids who want to have fun. Without basic knowledge of solfege and harmony, you cannot compose at a high level! In general, what he explains is funny! Yes, maybe for ordinary people it can pass as truth, but for professionals it's funny. Why is it even necessary for them to enter into some "image" created by the company? The company advertised them as composers and producers and they have to present themselves as such :( That's sad dude :(

text:
​@Ekaterina Georgieva  The garage band that he used was the first composing program that he know for the first time in his life when he was 15yo. He was self taught composing with garage band during his trainee by accident. And his Vical trainer which also music producer see his potential and began to teach him about composing ofc not with garage band.
I think you need to finish watching the full interview first.

Just some additional information about woozi that not discussed on this interview so you can know Woozi's music background before he join Pledis at 15yo

He first put interest in music after learning to play instruments such as piano, guitar, drums and clarinet in an English academy he used to attend when he was a kid.

Woozi competed in many classical music competitions when he was in elementary school until he was in the second grade of middle school.

He originally wanted to pursue a career as a classical musician.

With little expectation, he applied for Pledis Entertainment open audition. With a competition rate of 300:1, Woozi passed the audition and joined the agency in April 2011.

author: @KatieGeorgieva
text: @SimplySimran Dude, why are you arguing with me when you're a non professional? I graduated from the Central Music School in Moscow! Which is this school you can check yourself on Google. I was the first to be admitted to the Tchaikovsky Conservatory, which has rooms with the names of great composers and performers who studied there. You can check for yourself who they are. You can check for yourself who the professors are at this educational institution at the moment. And that's why I tell you that this boy tells stories for little children! If you're so stubborn, I can ask one of the professors of solfege or composition to write a short summary here so that you realize how ridiculous what he claims is!

author: @KatieGeorgieva
text: @@whoami8744 Dude, 15 is way too late to start composing! This is only possible if he has been a professional pianist for many years. Moreover, in order to use "Garage Band" without a piano, he must be an absolutist (a person with a perfect pitch). It also takes years to train an absolute (even though you are born one). That is why in music schools there are separate solfege groups for pianists and violinists (who must be absolute masters) and other instruments. Composition is taught in a separate group for theorists, and there solfeggio is twice as complex as that of absolutists, which, believe me, is incredibly complex. Do you want me to show you the program of the composition department at the Conservatory so that you realize how complex the theory of this discipline is? This boy claims to create complex songs. He does not compose children songs. For this reason, it is IMPOSSIBLE that they were created by a guy who two years ago learned to compose with "Garage Band"!

author: @KatieGeorgieva
text: @SimplySimran Dude, he claims he started at age 15 with no knowledge of solfege! Read my other comment to the other person I replied to. The theory of composers is very complex and is learned in early years. Again: if you want, I will download here the program of the composition department at the Tchaikovsky Conservatory so that you can see for yourself how complicated the theory is and how much is required to know how to compose at a high level. Seventeen's songs are complex enough to require at least a basic theoretical knowledge. Are you saying the songs are mediocre? Because with non-professional knowledge of composition, only children's songs can be created!

author: @waitwaitwaitholdon
text:
현재에 남고 싶다는 말을 들었을 때 안심이 되어서 눈물이 났어.
사실 꿈을 꿨거든.
오랜만에 나의 꿈에 나온 너는 미래의 자신에게 다급하게 물었어, 어떻게 해야할 지 모르겠다며 어떻게 이겨냈는지 물었어.
미래의 너와 과거의 너를 만나게 한 나로써는 미래에 영향이 끼칠까 다시 원래대로 돌렸어.
그리고 너무 서두르지 말라고, 힘듦을 이겨내는 것에 집착하지 말고 너의 속도대로 걸어도 된다는 말을 했지.
미래의 너는 내게 고맙다고 말해주었어.
꿈에서 깼을 땐 너무 놀라서 헉하고 깼어, 심장이 쿵 내려앉았어.
다른 건 몰라도 네가 겪었을 힘듦은 사실 같아서 너무 미안했어.
이를 내가 외면하고 있었던 것만 같아서. 너의 빛나는 모습만을 좇은 것만 같아서. 그래서 너무 미안했어.
타임머신을 탔을 때 언제로 가고 싶냐는 물음에 이 꿈이 바로 생각났지만 혹시라도 내가 꾸었던 꿈에서처럼 미래로 가고 싶어한다면 어떡하지라는 불안감이 밀려왔어.
하지만 너는 현재에 남고 싶다고 말해주었지.
그제서야 다시끔 깨달았어. 아, 내가 사랑하는 이유 중 하나가 이런 모습이었지. 하고.
고마워.
정말 고마워 지훈아.
나 또한 현재에 더 최선을 다하며 너를, 세븐틴을 사랑할게.
언제고 돌고 돌아 다시 네게로 갈게.

우아해 우리 지훈이
늘 행복 속에서 행복할 수 있도록 많은 행복을 안겨줄게.
빠르게 변하는 세상일지라도 우리만큼은 천천히 오래보자.
사랑해

text:
I enjoyed this episode. I love it when Suga and his guest talk about music because you see how interested and how close Suga listens to his guest, He listens closely to them all the time but, When it comes to music there is more of a comfort in the atmosphere, and a twinkle in Suga's eyes
Suga has such a great way to get guests to open up more about their music and life.  The way when some guests say they want to collaborate with Suga and he automatically tells he would like to do so,
Well, it warms my heart because you see the excitement in the guest's eyes.
Woozi is very talented and honestly, I did not know that he wrote and produced most of Seveteens's songs. he looks very young, But heck I wrote my first screenplay, directed, produced, and acted in the play at the age of 10 when I was in 4th grade so I feel that dearly.
I love seeing people chasing their dreams and making them true.
I want to wish Woozi, Seventeen, BTS, .and Suga the very best of luck in all they do.
I love you all

author: @jovitamanalo2707
text:
I couldn't help but smile while watching the video. I'm very happy and proud to call myself a CARAT. I appreciate Yoongi and the team for making this possible. I understood how challenging it must have been and how committed BTS and SEVENTEEN are to honing their craft and releasing music that resonates with the fans. I greatly value the team's effort and the progress our relationship has made between idol and fan. In the same way that you helped us when we were going through a difficult time, I hope we've helped you through yours as well. Please don’t worry about taking a break in your career to fulfill your duties to your country, we will be waiting patiently with you. Thank you so much! 

영상을 보면서 웃음을 참을 수 없었습니다. 스스로를 캐럿이라고 부르게 되어 매우 기쁘고 자랑스럽습니다. 이것을 가능하게 해준 Yoongi와 팀에 감사드립니다. 얼마나 힘들었을지, 방탄소년단과 세븐틴이 기술을 연마하고 팬들의 공감을 불러일으키는 음악을 발표하는 데 얼마나 헌신했는지 이해했습니다. 팀의 노력과 아이돌과 팬 사이의 관계 발전을 높이 평가합니다. 저희가 힘들 때 저희를 도와주신 것처럼 저희도 고객님의 도움이 되었기를 바랍니다. 귀하의 국가에 대한 의무를 다하기 위해 경력을 쉬는 것에 대해 걱정하지 마십시오. 인내심을 가지고 기다리고 있습니다. 매우 감사합니다!
